This paper discusses the current state and problems of style transfer research in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques for style transfer, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of style transfer, which can involve neural networks and optimization algorithms, topics that are also relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
